    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4727" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἴ̄λιος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝί̄λιος</span>) and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἴ̄λιον</span>
            (<i><span class="en">Il. 15.71</span></i>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Ilium</span>, a
          name for Troy derived from  that of its founder Ilus;
          epithets, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰπεινή, αἰπύ, ἐρατεινή, εὐτείχεος,
            ἠνεμόεσσα, ἱερή, ὀφρυόεσσα</span>. In wider signification, for
          the region about Troy, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.71</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 19.182</span></i>. In <i><span class="en">Il. 15.66</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.104</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 22.6</span></i>, the true form of the gen.
          is <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἰλίοο</span>, as the scansion shows (cf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Αἴολος</span>).</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
